    en: "Temporary workers have the same basic labor rights as permanent employees in New York. A temp worker is entitled to minimum wage, overtime, a safe workplace, and protection from discrimination. A staffing agency cannot charge fees for finding work, and both the agency and the company using the temp worker share responsibility for labor law violations."
